      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POPPY LANE (5) scored three runs back then missed the placings before bouncing back at her latest appearance over 1800m at this track, beaten a neck into second after being handy all the way. Needs to be at her best to beat this field but she has the ability to mix it with them. BALLADORO (3) led last time out and was successful in a far better performance at Port Pirie over 1609m, getting home by 5 metres. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Meeting a deeper field this time but he is up to the challenge. SHEZA CARONA (1) has a strong record here which is significant. Finished fifth over 1800m at this circuit last time out. Include from the coveted pegs draw. DIDMESELFAMISCHIEF (7) is worth plenty of thought off a last-start win by 2 metres at Port Pirie over 1609m. In the mix.",
